snippet.textDisplay:
Can't ppl stop talking about their couple and give the appreciation this collab deserve ??

I wasn't expecting Jihyo for this but I'm glad she's there, her dancing skills finally get the attention it deserves ! And her voice on this song wow ! Momo's voice, dance style and facial expression fit Taemin's song in fact, she shines a lot everytime she covers his songs ! What I regret is Jihyo and Momo were not in synch during their duo in the beginning it'd have been even visuallt prettier and stunning if they were but it still so good.
Taemin as always he's slaying everything, the way he moves when he's dancing is so gracious, elegant, he knows how interpret the song and share his feeling throught his dance -
I'd have loved if they sang the japanese version instead of the korean one but well it's a korean ceremony so it's understandable...

snippet.textDisplay:
By the way people should look into the lyrics 🙃
Yes the song's title is “Goodbye Loneliness" but it has absolutely the opposite meaning. There it's sung about the sadness of separation and that it's necessary for the happiness of both of them. It's said that one should not be afraid of separation and loneliness: sometimes it's better to leave but always remember what happened between them. Taemin sings about going further, not forgetting the past but letting go. He asks her (him, it doesn’t matter🙃) to remember that in any case she(he, it) is the best in the world.
